Problem Set 1

[70 pts] You are given a set of two text files of New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) data, NYSE_daily_prices.csv and NYSE_dividends.csv. You are required to create a Hive database containing two tables based on the text files, and then do some analysis of the data using Hive queries.

A

[6 pts] Download the data file, stock.zip, from the course website and unzip it in a local OS directory. Open the files in a text editor to see how the data fields are separated. Create an HDFS directory, HW3, right below the CentOS root. In HW3, create a directory called stockdata. Use the File View in Ambari to upload the two data files into stockdata. Display a screenshot (in Ambari) showing all these files in the /HW3/stockdata directory (your screenshot should show this directory).

[root@sandbox ~]# hadoop fs -mkdir /HW3
[root@sandbox ~]# hadoop fs -mkdir /HW3/stockdata

B

[13 pts] Create a Hive database called stocksdb located in HW3. In the stocksdb database, use Hive command line interface to create two tables stock_prices and stock_dividends. The stock_dividends contains the columns in the following order: exchng, symbol, ymd, and dividend. The data type of dividend is DOUBLE. Describe these two tables in Hive command line interface, and attach one single screenshot, showing the commands and the results.

Problem Set 2

[30 pts] You are given a text file (flight12.csv) of flight delays and are required to create a Hive table using regular expressions, and then do some queries on the table.

A

[5 pts] Download the data file and use the File View in Ambari to load the file into HDFS in the HW3 directory. Create a Hive database called flightsdb located in HW3, and then in flightsdb create a Hive table, flight_delays_hw3. This table has the following columns: ymd, flight_num, carrier_delay, weather_delay, nas_delay, security_delay, and late_aircraft_delay. The first two columns are of the STRING data type and the other columns are of the DOUBLE data type.

hive> CREATE DATABASE flightsdb

OK

    >   nas_delay DOUBLE,
    >   security_delay DOUBLE,

[15 pts] Insert data into flight_delays_hw3 by extracting it from temp_flight with regular expression (regexp_extract()) calls. The data fields are separated by commas. You are required to extract fields 2, 5, 19, 20, 21, 22 and 23 to populate your table.

hive> INSERT OVERWRITE TABLE flightsdb.flight_delays_hw3
    > SELECT
    >   regexp_extract(col_value, '^(?:([^,]*)\,?){2}', 1) ymd,
    >   regexp_extract(col_value, '^(?:([^,]*)\,?){5}', 1) flight_num,
    >   regexp_extract(col_value, '^(?:([^,]*)\,?){19}', 1) carrier_delay,
    >   regexp_extract(col_value, '^(?:([^,]*)\,?){20}', 1) weather_delay,
    >   regexp_extract(col_value, '^(?:([^,]*)\,?){21}', 1) nas_delay,
    >   regexp_extract(col_value, '^(?:([^,]*)\,?){22}', 1) security_delay,
    >   regexp_extract(col_value, '^(?:([^,]*)\,?){23}', 1) late_aircraft_delay
